/*!
\page dash-test Dash Test
This information pertains to building Diamond for OS X.


<h3>Compiler & Autotools</h3>

Xcode does not install Autotools, which is required to build the Diamond Editor. Use MacPorts or the equivalent
to install Autotools. 

The Diamond Editor requires Apple Clang version 4.2 or newer.&nbsp;&nbsp;

MacPorts can be downloaded and installed from
<a class="www-link" href="http://www.macports.org">MacPorts</a>

The following is a straight forward guide for installing MacPorts
<a class="www-link" href="http://guide.macports.org">MacPorts Guide</a>

Using MacPorts, install the ports listed below. MacPorts will automatically adjust your PATH for Automake and Autoconf.

  \li sudo port install automake
  \li sudo port install autoconf   

Compiling with Clang will require the following environment variables.

  \li CC=clang
  \li CXX=clang++
  \li OBJCXX=clang++

Alternatively, &ndash;&ndash; &ndash;&ndash;&ndash;  Are there dashes or ndash?


\code
CC=clang   CXX=clang++   OBJCXX=clang++   --prefix $HOME/cs_lib
\endcode

<br>

